WEBVTT

00:07.924 --> 00:11.886
♪ ♪

00:33.950 --> 00:36.744
[WOMAN ON P.A.]: PAGING DR. MALCOLM TO ROOM 413.

00:36.745 --> 00:37.745
DR. MALCOLM...

00:37.746 --> 00:38.746
THOUGHT I MIGHTFIND YOU HERE.

00:38.747 --> 00:40.123
HIYA, DOC.

00:40.165 --> 00:41.166
HOW ARE YOU FEELINGTODAY, HENRY?

00:41.207 --> 00:42.125
NOT TOO BAD.

00:42.167 --> 00:43.918
BETTER THAN YESTERDAY.

00:43.960 --> 00:45.211
WELL, NOW THATYOU'RE UP AND WALKING,

00:45.253 --> 00:46.629
I THOUGHT I'D GET YOU STARTEDON REHAB TOMORROW.

00:46.671 --> 00:48.631
HOW DOES THAT SOUND?

00:48.673 --> 00:49.632
GOOD ENOUGH

00:49.674 --> 00:50.633
TO GIVE YOU MY DESSERT,

00:50.675 --> 00:51.634
AND BELIEVE ME,

00:51.676 --> 00:52.635
IT WAS THE BEST THING

00:52.677 --> 00:53.636
ON MY TRAY THIS AFTERNOON.

00:53.678 --> 00:54.637
I REALLY APPRECIATE THE OFFER,

00:54.679 --> 00:56.096
BUT I DON'T WANTTO SPOIL MY DINNER.

00:56.097 --> 00:57.849
I HAVE AN EIGHT-YEAR-OLDWAITING FOR ME AT HOME.

00:57.891 --> 00:59.017
WELL, SEE YOU TOMORROW.

00:59.058 --> 01:00.060
YOU BET.

01:02.604 --> 01:05.272
[P.A.]: PAGING DR. GILSON TO EMERGENCY.

01:05.272 --> 01:06.316
DR. GILSON.

01:11.988 --> 01:12.947
HEY, JIM.

01:12.989 --> 01:14.949
HEY, DR. GILSON, WE HAVE AN APPENDECTOMY.

01:14.991 --> 01:16.283
22-YEAR-OLD MALE.

01:16.284 --> 01:17.786
I KNOW YOU'VE BEEN HERESINCE 7:00 THIS MORNING,

01:17.827 --> 01:18.952
AND I WOULDN'T ASK,

01:18.953 --> 01:21.498
BUT THE ON-CALL SURGEONIS STUCK IN TRAFFIC, SO.

01:21.539 --> 01:23.666
I'M SUPPOSED TO BE GOING HOMETO HAVE DINNER WITH MY SON.

01:25.001 --> 01:26.377
I JUST NEEDTO MAKE A CALL FIRST.

01:26.419 --> 01:27.796
THANK YOU.I WILL LET THE PATIENT KNOW

01:27.837 --> 01:29.506
WE'VE GOT ONE OFOUR BEST SURGEONS COMING IN.

01:29.547 --> 01:30.882
[P.A.]: PAGING DR. WEST.

01:30.924 --> 01:32.342
NURSES' STATION 2.

01:34.928 --> 01:37.471
[DOOR OPENS]

01:37.472 --> 01:39.682
[DOOR CLOSES]

01:39.724 --> 01:41.476
I'M SORRY I'M SO LATE, RUTH.

01:41.518 --> 01:43.311
[RUTH]: IT IS NOT A PROBLEM.

01:44.479 --> 01:45.479
HOW WAS ANDY TONIGHT?

01:45.480 --> 01:47.857
A LITTLE ON THE QUIET SIDE.

01:47.899 --> 01:49.316
WELL, I'LL SEE YOUTOMORROW.

01:49.317 --> 01:51.820
OH, THERE'S A PLATE FOR YOUIN THE OVEN.

01:51.861 --> 01:53.320
ALL YOU HAVE TO DOIS HEAT IT UP.

01:53.321 --> 01:54.239
HOW DID YOU KNOW

01:54.280 --> 01:55.240
THAT I WOULDN'T HAVE TIMETO EAT?

01:56.491 --> 01:57.992
WELL, I'VE WORKED FOR YOULONG ENOUGH TO FIGURE THAT OUT.

01:58.034 --> 01:59.744
THANK YOU SO MUCH...

01:59.786 --> 02:00.829
FOR EVERYTHING.

02:00.870 --> 02:01.830
GET SOME SLEEP.

02:01.871 --> 02:03.373
THANK YOU.

02:03.414 --> 02:04.833
I'LL TRY.

02:08.794 --> 02:10.088
-BYE.-BYE.

02:30.358 --> 02:31.734
I LOVE YOU.

02:43.955 --> 02:45.331
[SKYPE CHIMES]

02:50.044 --> 02:51.045
HI, HONEY!

02:51.087 --> 02:52.255
HI, MOM.

02:52.297 --> 02:53.923
IS EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT? WHY ARE YOU CALLING SO LATE?

02:53.965 --> 02:55.133
SHOOT.

02:55.175 --> 02:56.593
I ALWAYS FORGET WHETHER WE'RE EIGHT HOURS AHEAD

02:56.634 --> 02:57.635
OR BEHIND YOU.

02:57.677 --> 02:59.887
CAMEROON IS EIGHT HOURS AHEAD.

02:59.888 --> 03:00.888
HOW'S DAD?

03:00.889 --> 03:01.889
OH, HE'S GREAT,

03:01.890 --> 03:02.932
BUT HOW ARE YOU?

03:02.974 --> 03:04.391
YOU LOOK TIRED.

03:04.392 --> 03:05.226
IT'S BEEN A ROUGH DAY.

03:05.268 --> 03:07.060
I HAD SEVEN SURGERIES,

03:07.061 --> 03:09.606
A BOARD MEETING, AND ROUNDS, SO...

03:09.647 --> 03:11.316
I DIDN'T MAKE IT HOMEBEFORE ANDY WENT TO BED...

03:11.357 --> 03:12.400
AGAIN.

03:12.442 --> 03:13.610
WELL, THAT CAN'T BE GOOD FOR YOU...

03:13.651 --> 03:14.611
OR FOR ANDY.

03:14.652 --> 03:16.070
ANDY'S DOING OKAY.

03:16.112 --> 03:18.906
YOU NEED TO TAKE SOME TIME OFF AND RELAX.

03:18.907 --> 03:21.618
DOESN'T ANDY HAVE A FALL BREAK COMING UP?

03:21.659 --> 03:22.660
YEAH, HE DOES,

03:22.702 --> 03:25.455
BUT I JUST...

03:25.496 --> 03:26.747
I DON'T HAVE TIME, YOU KNOW?

03:26.748 --> 03:28.415
I HAVE PATIENTS, AND...

03:28.416 --> 03:31.251
AND YOU'RE NOT THE ONLY SURGEON IN SEATTLE.

03:31.252 --> 03:33.086
THEY'LL FIND SOMEONE TO COVER FOR YOU.

03:33.087 --> 03:34.839
I HAVEN'T BEEN UP THEREIN YEARS.

03:34.881 --> 03:37.300
I DON'T EVEN KNOWIF ANDY WOULD LIKE IT, AND...

03:40.053 --> 03:40.970
I DON'T KNOW, MOM.

03:41.012 --> 03:42.262
IT'S PROBABLYA PRETTY CRAZY IDEA.

03:42.263 --> 03:44.098
NO, WHAT'S CRAZY

03:44.140 --> 03:47.393
IS YOU BURNING YOURSELF OUT LIKE THIS...

03:47.435 --> 03:48.937
AND BURNING YOUR HOUSE DOWN.

03:48.978 --> 03:50.813
IS THAT SMOKE I SEE BEHIND YOU?

03:50.855 --> 03:52.273
JUST MY DINNER BURNING.

03:52.315 --> 03:53.441
[LAUGHS]

03:53.483 --> 03:55.442
YOU KNOW WHAT, MOM? I'M GOING TO CALL YOU BACK.

03:55.443 --> 03:56.277
LOVE YOU.

03:56.319 --> 03:57.612
[SMOKE ALARM BEEPS]

03:57.654 --> 03:58.696
OH...

04:05.286 --> 04:06.537
OKAY, HURRY UP, ANDY.WE DON'T WANT TO BE LATE.

04:06.579 --> 04:08.164
OH!

04:08.206 --> 04:09.123
IT'S OKAY.

04:15.755 --> 04:16.880
WHEN WAS THIS?

04:16.923 --> 04:18.257
YESTERDAY.

04:20.385 --> 04:21.969
HONEY, YOU WERE IN THIS?

04:21.970 --> 04:23.721
YEAH. THE WHOLE CLASS WAS.

04:23.763 --> 04:25.306
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL MEABOUT IT?

04:25.348 --> 04:26.807
YOU WERE WORKING.

04:26.808 --> 04:28.851
HONEY, I WOULD HAVEMADE TIME FOR THIS.

04:28.893 --> 04:30.561
YOU MISSED MY SPELLING BEE,

04:30.603 --> 04:32.313
SO...

04:32.355 --> 04:34.649
I DIDN'T THINKYOU COULD COME FOR THIS.

04:34.691 --> 04:37.819
LISTEN, I KNOW I MISSED THAT, BUT I TOLD YOU HOW SORRY I WAS.

04:37.860 --> 04:39.319
I HAD AN EMERGENCY SURGERY.

04:39.320 --> 04:41.072
IT'S NO BIG DEAL.

04:50.832 --> 04:54.835
[P.A.]: PAGING DR. ROTHSTEIN.

04:54.836 --> 04:55.920
DR. ROTHSTEIN...

04:55.962 --> 04:56.921
DR. GILSON!

04:56.963 --> 04:58.006
HI.

04:58.047 --> 04:59.424
HI...

04:59.465 --> 05:01.050
SHEILA MYMAN.

05:01.092 --> 05:03.845
YOU REMOVED MY KIDNEY STONESLAST MONTH.

05:03.886 --> 05:05.263
YES, OF COURSE.

05:05.305 --> 05:07.390
WHAT ARE YOU DOING BACK HERE? YOU'RE NOT SICK AGAIN, I HOPE.

05:07.432 --> 05:08.558
NO, JUST VISITING A FRIEND.

05:08.599 --> 05:10.560
OH, WELL, I HOPEYOUR FRIEND FEELS BETTER,

05:10.601 --> 05:12.312
AND IF THERE'S ANYTHINGI CAN DO, LET ME KNOW.

05:12.353 --> 05:13.855
[P.A.]: DR. MATLETS, RECOVERY ROOM 6.

05:13.896 --> 05:17.442
DR. MATLETS, RECOVERY ROOM 6.

05:20.236 --> 05:22.697
DO YOU REMEMBERSHEILA MYMAN?

05:22.739 --> 05:24.240
YES.NICE WOMAN.

05:24.282 --> 05:25.950
KIDNEY STONES LAST MONTH.WHY?

05:25.992 --> 05:27.285
I JUST PASSED HERIN THE HALL,

05:27.326 --> 05:28.702
I HAD NO IDEA WHO SHE WAS.

05:28.703 --> 05:30.537
IT'S MY JOB TO KEEPALL THE PATIENTS STRAIGHT,

05:30.538 --> 05:32.790
AND TO KEEP YOU ON SCHEDULE.

05:32.832 --> 05:34.167
WELL, MOVING FORWARD,

05:34.208 --> 05:36.044
COULD YOU PLEASE SCHEDULEA LITTLE MORE TIME FOR ME

05:36.085 --> 05:37.628
TO GET TO KNOW THEM?

05:37.670 --> 05:39.880
YOU'RE A GENERAL SURGEON,

05:39.881 --> 05:41.549
NOT A GENERAL PRACTITIONER.

05:41.591 --> 05:42.800
YOU DON'T HAVETHAT KIND OF TIME.

05:43.885 --> 05:44.761
DR. WEBER IS WONDERING

05:44.802 --> 05:46.804
IF YOU CAN COVER FOR HIMTHIS WEEKEND

05:46.846 --> 05:47.888
AND BE ON-CALL?

05:47.889 --> 05:49.056
DOESN'T ANYONE THINKI HAVE A LIFE

05:49.057 --> 05:50.475
OUTSIDE OFTHIS HOSPITAL?

05:50.516 --> 05:52.435
UNLESS NO ONE ELSE CAN DO IT.

05:58.900 --> 06:00.735
WOULD YOU BE ABLE TO CLEARMY SCHEDULE

06:00.777 --> 06:02.195
THE WEEK OF ANDY'S SCHOOL BREAK?

06:03.362 --> 06:04.405
IT WON'T BE EASY,

06:04.447 --> 06:06.282
BUT I'VE BEEN KNOWNTO WORK A MIRACLE OR TWO.

06:07.325 --> 06:08.575
GREAT.

06:08.576 --> 06:09.786
I THINK I'M GOINGTO TAKE MY MOM'S ADVICE

06:09.827 --> 06:11.621
AND DO SOMETHINGFOR ANDY AND MYSELF.

06:14.540 --> 06:15.666
DON'T FORGETABOUT THE NEW PROMOTION.

06:15.708 --> 06:18.795
THEY'RE STILL CIRCLINGCANDIDATES FOR THE SPOT.

06:18.836 --> 06:20.505
IT'S A WEEKOF OWED VACATION TIME,

06:20.546 --> 06:22.173
SO IT SHOULDN'T AFFECTTHEIR DECISION.

06:30.306 --> 06:32.141
OKAY...

06:32.183 --> 06:34.435
ANYTHING ELSEYOU WANT ME TO PACK?

06:36.396 --> 06:39.440
YOU'RE NOT GOING TO NEEDSWIM TRUNKS ON THE FARM.

06:39.482 --> 06:41.901
IF WE WERE GOINGTO FLORIDA OR HAWAII

06:41.943 --> 06:43.444
LIKE SOME OF MY FRIENDS,

06:43.486 --> 06:44.654
INSTEAD OF A FARM,

06:44.695 --> 06:45.613
WE WOULD.

06:45.655 --> 06:47.615
WELL, IT'S NOT JUST A FARM.

06:47.657 --> 06:49.659
IT'S OUR FAMILY'S FARM.

06:49.700 --> 06:52.328
ARE YOU SURE YOU WOULDN'TRATHER GO TO HAWAII?

06:52.370 --> 06:54.121
HA HA, NICE TRY,

06:54.122 --> 06:56.165
BUT I CAN'T GO TOO FARFROM THE HOSPITAL, OKAY?

06:56.207 --> 06:57.917
THE FARM'S ONLYA COUPLE OF HOURS AWAY.

07:00.336 --> 07:01.462
IT'LL BE FUN, YOU'LL SEE,

07:01.504 --> 07:03.631
AND WE MIGHT EVEN BE THEREAROUND HARVEST TIME.

07:03.673 --> 07:06.967
I'M JUST EXCITEDTO SPEND TIME WITH YOU, MOM.

07:06.968 --> 07:10.012
ME TOO, ANDY.

07:10.054 --> 07:11.013
ME TOO.

07:21.315 --> 07:23.317
I FORGOTHOW MUCH I LOVE IT HERE.

07:26.946 --> 07:28.239
THERE ARE A LOT OF TREES.

07:28.281 --> 07:29.282
THERE SURE ARE.

07:29.323 --> 07:30.158
DO YOU KNOWWHAT KIND OF TREES THEY ARE?

07:30.199 --> 07:31.033
PINE!

07:31.075 --> 07:31.909
THAT'S RIGHT.

07:31.951 --> 07:33.494
YOU ARE SO SMART.

07:33.536 --> 07:36.372
IS THAT WHY THE TOWN'SCALLED PINEVIEW?

07:36.414 --> 07:39.250
SEE, YOU'RE ALREADY STARTINGTO APPRECIATE IT.

08:00.646 --> 08:02.064
[ANDY]: MOM, ARE WE LOST?

08:02.106 --> 08:04.358
NO, I'VE BEEN FOLLOWINGALL THE SIGNS.

08:04.400 --> 08:08.279
IT JUST SEEMS LIKE WE'VE BEENON THIS ROAD FOR A LONG TIME.

08:10.907 --> 08:12.700
WHAT IS THIS GUY DOING?

08:19.624 --> 08:20.917
UH-OH.

08:20.958 --> 08:22.376
[SIGHS]

08:22.418 --> 08:24.795
JUST STAY IN THE CAR, OKAY? I'VE GOT THIS.

08:30.218 --> 08:31.885
IT'S A ONE-LANE ROAD.

08:31.886 --> 08:33.261
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO YIELDTO ONCOMING VEHICLES.

08:33.304 --> 08:34.263
I KNOW.

08:34.304 --> 08:36.057
OKAY, SO WHY AREN'TYOU YIELDING?

08:36.097 --> 08:37.724
BECAUSE I GOT HERE FIRST.

08:37.725 --> 08:39.434
IT'S NOT ABOUTWHO GOT HERE FIRST.

08:39.477 --> 08:40.852
YOU HAVE A YIELD SIGN, AND I DON'T.

08:43.688 --> 08:45.149
SO YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO BACK UPAND PULL OVER.

08:45.191 --> 08:47.318
OR... YOU COULD.

08:49.070 --> 08:50.279
I'M GOING TO TAKE A WILD GUESS

08:50.321 --> 08:51.781
AND SAY THAT YOU'RE NOTFROM AROUND HERE, ARE YOU?

08:51.822 --> 08:52.949
NO, I'M NOT,

08:52.990 --> 08:54.074
BUT WHAT DIFFERENCEDOES THAT MAKE?

08:54.075 --> 08:56.743
BESIDES, I HAVE A CHILD IN MY CAR,

08:56.744 --> 08:58.578
AND I DON'T WANT TO RISKGOING INTO A DITCH

08:58.579 --> 09:00.248
OR GETTING A FLATOR SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

09:00.289 --> 09:01.749
AH... NOT LIKELY.

09:01.791 --> 09:02.959
OKAY, WELL THEN...

09:03.000 --> 09:04.627
WHY DON'T YOU SHOW MEHOW IT'S DONE?

09:04.669 --> 09:06.254
YOU KNOW, SO I'LL KNOW FOR NEXT TIME?

09:08.673 --> 09:09.632
OKAY.

09:15.721 --> 09:17.431
[STARTS ENGINE]

09:28.901 --> 09:30.945
[AIR HISSING]

09:34.865 --> 09:35.866
OH...

09:38.703 --> 09:41.122
LOOKS LIKE I GOT A FLAT.

09:41.163 --> 09:43.165
I FEEL TERRIBLE.CAN WE AT LEAST GIVE YOU A LIFT?

09:44.250 --> 09:45.293
I'LL BE FINE.

09:45.334 --> 09:46.877
JUST TAKE IT EASYON THE NEXT GUY, ALL RIGHT?

09:46.919 --> 09:49.171
YEAH, ABSOLUTELY, OF COURSE...

09:49.213 --> 09:50.590
AND AGAIN, I'M REALLY SORRY.

10:21.704 --> 10:23.164
SO, WHAT DO YOU THINK?

10:23.205 --> 10:25.666
IT'S BIG.

10:25.708 --> 10:27.043
COME ON, LET'SGO FIND THE KEY.

10:27.084 --> 10:28.002
YOUR GRANDMA SAID

10:28.044 --> 10:30.212
IT'S WHERE WE ALWAYSUSED TO KEEP IT.

10:30.254 --> 10:32.256
WAS I EVER HERE BEFORE?

10:32.298 --> 10:33.257
YOUR DADDY AND IBROUGHT YOU HERE

10:33.299 --> 10:35.092
WHEN YOU WEREVERY LITTLE.

10:35.134 --> 10:37.887
YOUR GREAT-GRANDPA GILSON, WHO WAS MY GRANDPA,

10:37.928 --> 10:39.513
WAS STILL ALIVEBACK THEN,

10:39.555 --> 10:41.682
AND WE HADTHANKSGIVING HERE.

10:41.724 --> 10:42.975
I DON'T REMEMBER.

10:43.017 --> 10:44.101
OF COURSE, YOU DON'T.

10:44.143 --> 10:45.728
YOU WERE ONLY A YEARAND A HALF OLD,

10:45.770 --> 10:47.438
BUT THERE ARE PLENTYOF PICTURES INSIDE.

10:47.480 --> 10:49.315
AT LEAST, THERE USED TO BE.

10:50.483 --> 10:51.609
YOU SEE THAT?

10:51.650 --> 10:53.069
I DID THAT WHENI WAS YOUR AGE.

10:53.110 --> 10:56.196
I WAS RUNNING AROUNDOUTSIDE, PLAYING,

10:56.197 --> 10:57.698
AND THEY TOLD METO STAY OFF THE PORCH,

10:57.740 --> 11:01.034
AND I DIDN'T LISTEN, AND THE POOR GUY LOST HIS NOSE.

11:01.035 --> 11:02.203
DID YOU GET IN TROUBLE?

11:02.244 --> 11:04.580
I DIDN'T GET DESSERTTHAT NIGHT,

11:04.622 --> 11:06.791
AND YOUR GREAT-GRANDMA GILSON'SPEAR COBBLER

11:06.832 --> 11:08.876
WAS THE BEST THINGYOU'VE EVER TASTED.

11:08.918 --> 11:10.043
EVER!

11:10.044 --> 11:11.128
[LAUGHS]

11:13.673 --> 11:15.715
RIGHT WHERE GRANDMASAID IT WOULD BE.

11:15.716 --> 11:17.677
COME ON, LET'S GO INSIDE.

11:22.556 --> 11:24.392
OKAY!

11:26.227 --> 11:27.560
WHY DON'T YOU TAKETHE BEDROOM UPSTAIRS,

11:27.561 --> 11:28.771
THE FIRST ONEON THE RIGHT?

11:28.813 --> 11:30.272
THAT'S MY OLD ROOM.

11:30.314 --> 11:32.732
IT'S NOT A GIRL'S ROOM, IS IT?

11:32.733 --> 11:33.651
YOU'RE SAFE.

11:33.692 --> 11:36.237
IT WAS REDONEYEARS AGO.

12:06.225 --> 12:07.601
AND YOU SEE THESE TREESOVER HERE?

12:07.643 --> 12:11.480
I PLANTED THESEWITH GREAT-GRANDPA GILSON.

12:14.358 --> 12:15.317
HEY!

12:15.359 --> 12:17.944
WHAT ARE YOUSO INTERESTED IN, HMM?

12:17.945 --> 12:20.698
I WAS JUST WONDERINGWHAT THAT MAN WAS DOING?

12:23.826 --> 12:25.785
I THINKHE'S STEALING OUR PEARS.

12:25.786 --> 12:27.288
LOOK,

12:27.329 --> 12:28.706
GO OVER THEREAND CALL THE SHERIFF,

12:28.748 --> 12:29.790
AND TELL HIM

12:29.832 --> 12:31.125
THAT WE HAVE A PEAR THIEFIN GILSON ORCHARD,

12:31.167 --> 12:32.585
AND TO COME QUICK.

12:44.680 --> 12:46.807
LOOK, I DON'T KNOWWHO YOU THINK YOU ARE,

12:46.849 --> 12:48.100
BUT THIS IS PRIVATE PROPERTY.

12:48.142 --> 12:50.102
YOU CAN'T GO AROUND PICKINGOTHER PEOPLE'S FRUIT.

12:50.144 --> 12:52.563
I CAN IF I WORK HERE.

12:55.274 --> 12:56.484
YOU?

12:56.525 --> 12:58.527
YEP, ME.

12:58.569 --> 13:00.362
IF IT ISN'T THE ROAD HOG.

13:00.404 --> 13:04.200
AH... LISTEN, I AM SO SORRY ABOUT THAT FLAT.

13:04.241 --> 13:06.327
I HOPE YOU WERE ABLETO CHANGE IT ALL RIGHT.

13:06.368 --> 13:07.703
WELL...

13:07.745 --> 13:09.580
A HALF AN HOUR OF MY TIME, AND I WAS ALL GOOD.

13:09.622 --> 13:11.749
I'D BE HAPPY TO PAY FOR IT... THE TIRE?

13:11.791 --> 13:13.334
NOT NECESSARY.

13:13.375 --> 13:14.543
LONG AS YOU LEARNEDTHE RULES OF THE ROAD.

13:15.628 --> 13:18.171
YEAH, I DID.I DID INDEED, MR...?

13:18.172 --> 13:21.467
WILL NASH.I MANAGE THE FARM HERE.

13:22.927 --> 13:24.344
I TAKE IT YOU'RE GRACEAND ELI'S DAUGHTER.

13:24.345 --> 13:25.721
[SMILES AWKWARDLY]

13:25.763 --> 13:27.348
YEAH, THEY DIDN'T TELL MEYOU WERE COMING.

13:27.389 --> 13:28.933
MY MOM WAS SUPPOSEDTO CALL YOU,

13:28.974 --> 13:30.392
BUT SHE CAN BEKIND OF FORGETFUL,

13:30.434 --> 13:31.977
SO I'M NOT REALLY SURPRISED.

13:33.562 --> 13:34.854
UM, LISTEN, MY SON AND I,

13:34.855 --> 13:36.732
WE ARE ONLY GOING TO BE HEREFOR A WEEK,

13:36.774 --> 13:37.817
SO YOU DON'T HAVE TO WORRYABOUT US.

13:37.858 --> 13:39.276
HOPEFULLY, WE'LL STAYOUT OF YOUR WAY.

13:39.318 --> 13:41.237
I'M SURE IT'LL BE FINE.

13:41.278 --> 13:42.279
[CAR DOOR CLOSING]

13:44.073 --> 13:45.366
I TAKE ITYOU'RE THE YOUNG FELLA

13:45.407 --> 13:47.200
WHO CALLED ABOUT A PEAR THIEF?

13:47.201 --> 13:48.202
I'M SO SORRY.

13:48.244 --> 13:50.037
[SHERIFF]: HEY, WILL.

13:52.081 --> 13:53.791
YOU CALLEDTHE SHERIFF ON ME?

13:53.832 --> 13:58.003
LISTEN, THIS WAS JUSTA REALLY BIG MISUNDERSTANDING.

13:58.045 --> 13:59.630
MM.

13:59.672 --> 14:03.216
WILL MAY BE A LOT OF THINGS, BUT HE'S NO THIEF.

14:03.217 --> 14:04.927
[LAUGHS]

14:04.969 --> 14:07.721
SO, IF THERE ARE NO ARRESTSTO BE MADE,

14:07.763 --> 14:10.223
I'M GOING TO HEAD BACKINTO TOWN.

14:10.224 --> 14:12.601
OKAY, THANKS.SORRY.

14:12.643 --> 14:14.061
[CHUCKLES]

14:14.103 --> 14:15.396
UM...

14:15.437 --> 14:17.231
ANDY, THIS IS WILL.

14:17.273 --> 14:18.607
HE MANAGES THE FARM,

14:18.649 --> 14:19.732
AND WE ARE GOING

14:19.733 --> 14:21.735
TO STAY OUT OF HIS WAYTHIS WEEK, OKAY?

14:21.777 --> 14:23.904
OH, ANDY!

14:23.946 --> 14:24.822
CATCH.

14:26.198 --> 14:28.450
THANKS, WILL.I WAS GETTING HUNGRY.

14:29.493 --> 14:30.452
SORRY!

14:38.252 --> 14:40.254
YOU KNOW, I WAS SURPRISEDWHEN I HEARD YOU RETIRED.

14:40.296 --> 14:41.255
I NEVER THOUGHT

14:41.297 --> 14:42.422
YOU WERE GOINGTO LEAVE THE FARM.

14:42.423 --> 14:43.799
NEITHER DID I,

14:43.841 --> 14:46.593
BUT THESE OLDBONES DID ME IN.

14:46.594 --> 14:49.262
BEEN A LONG TIMESINCE I SAW YOU, THOUGH,

14:49.263 --> 14:52.766
AND ANDY, YOU WERE JUSTA BABY LAST TIME WE MET.

14:52.808 --> 14:54.476
SO YOU KNEW MY GREAT-GRANDPA?

14:54.518 --> 14:56.061
SURE DID!

14:56.103 --> 14:57.937
I'VE KNOWNFOUR GENERATIONS OF GILSONS.

14:57.938 --> 15:01.608
I'VE MANAGED THE GILSON FARMFOR OVER 40 YEARS.

15:01.609 --> 15:02.651
WOW.

15:02.693 --> 15:05.112
I WAS FIRST HIREDBY YOUR GREAT-GRANDPARENTS,

15:05.154 --> 15:06.655
AND WHEN YOUR GRANDPAINHERITED THE FARM,

15:06.697 --> 15:07.947
HE MADE ME MANAGER,

15:07.948 --> 15:09.658
BECAUSE HE AND YOUR GRANDMALIVED IN SEATTLE.

15:09.700 --> 15:11.160
MM-HMM.

15:11.201 --> 15:13.119
YOUR MOMWAS THE THIRD GENERATION,

15:13.120 --> 15:14.621
AND NOW YOU'RE THE FOURTH.

15:14.622 --> 15:16.206
THAT'S PRETTY COOL.

15:19.043 --> 15:21.462
CAN I GO CHECKTHINGS OUT?

15:21.503 --> 15:24.631
SURE! LOTS TO SEE AROUND HERE.

15:24.632 --> 15:25.507
CAN I, MOM?

15:25.549 --> 15:26.800
MM-HMM.

15:26.842 --> 15:28.636
[LAUGHS]

15:32.556 --> 15:33.724
SO...

15:38.020 --> 15:38.979
I TAKE IT YOU MET WILL.

15:38.980 --> 15:42.983
YES, I HAVE.MM-HMM.

15:43.025 --> 15:44.151
MOM TOLD ME

15:44.193 --> 15:45.318
THAT YOU HANDPICKED HIMTO BE YOUR REPLACEMENT?

15:45.319 --> 15:47.320
WE WERE LUCKY TO GET HIM.

15:47.321 --> 15:49.698
I HAD TO DO SOME FAST TALKINGTO CONVINCE HIM TO TAKE THE JOB.

15:49.740 --> 15:51.241
IS THAT SO?

15:51.283 --> 15:54.662
NOT EVERY DAY YOU FINDA FOURTH-GENERATION FARMER

15:54.703 --> 15:57.081
WHO ALSO HAPPENSTO BE AN AGRONOMIST.

15:57.122 --> 15:58.665
WILL IS A SCIENTIST?

15:58.666 --> 16:01.335
YOU SHOULD HEAR HIM TALKABOUT SOIL ACIDITY,

16:01.377 --> 16:04.337
CROSS-POLLINATION, HYBRID SEEDS...

16:04.338 --> 16:05.381
[LAUGHS]

16:05.422 --> 16:06.632
I DON'T UNDERSTANDTHE HALF OF IT.

16:06.674 --> 16:08.092
HUH.

16:09.760 --> 16:11.344
HOW COME HE DOESN'T HAVEHIS OWN FARM?

16:11.345 --> 16:13.013
THE RECESSION.

16:13.055 --> 16:14.514
A LOT OF THE FARMS AROUND HEREGOT BOUGHT UP

16:14.515 --> 16:15.891
BY THESE BIG CORPORATIONS

16:15.933 --> 16:17.893
THAT SWOOPED INWHEN THE OPPORTUNITY WAS RIGHT,

16:17.935 --> 16:20.104
AND QUITE A FEW FAMILIESENDED UP MOVING AWAY,

16:20.145 --> 16:21.397
INCLUDING HIS.

16:21.438 --> 16:24.358
MUST BE TOUGH... LOSING YOUR FAMILY FARM.

16:24.400 --> 16:25.734
BUT AFTER COLLEGE,

16:25.776 --> 16:27.194
WILL CAME BACKDETERMINED

16:27.236 --> 16:30.197
TO REBUILD HISFAMILY'S LEGACY,

16:30.239 --> 16:33.032
AND LUCKYFOR THE GILSONS,

16:33.033 --> 16:34.952
HE IS NOW ON YOUR FARM.

16:34.994 --> 16:36.453
[LAUGHS]

16:36.495 --> 16:38.956
MOM, LOOK WHAT I FOUND!

16:56.432 --> 16:58.767
[WOMAN]: OH, SWEETIE, ARE YOU OKAY?

16:58.809 --> 17:00.436
YOU TOOK A BIG FALL THERE, DIDN'T YOU?

17:00.477 --> 17:01.812
[BOY]: OUCH! MOM, THAT HURTS!

17:01.854 --> 17:03.772
HI. IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

17:03.814 --> 17:05.398
I'M A DOCTOR.MAYBE I CAN HELP.

17:05.441 --> 17:06.566
OH, YES.

17:06.567 --> 17:09.068
MY SON, BOBBY, FELLAND SCRAPED HIS KNEE.

17:09.069 --> 17:10.319
OKAY.

17:10.362 --> 17:13.740
HI. HI, BOBBY, I'M DR. GILSON.THIS IS MY SON, ANDY.

17:13.741 --> 17:15.074
DO YOU MIND IF I TAKEA LOOK AT YOUR KNEE?

17:15.075 --> 17:16.326
SURE.

17:16.367 --> 17:19.997
ANDY, MAYBE YOU AND BOBBYWOULD LIKE ONE OF THESE, HMM?

17:20.038 --> 17:21.248
IS THAT OKAY?

17:21.290 --> 17:22.583
YEAH.

17:22.624 --> 17:23.666
HEY, YOU WANTTO DRAW WITH ME?

17:23.709 --> 17:24.710
SURE.

17:24.752 --> 17:28.130
I'M GOING TO TAKE A LOOKAT YOUR KNEE, OKAY?

17:28.172 --> 17:29.339
IT'S NOT BLEEDING.

17:29.381 --> 17:31.758
COULD YOU STRAIGHTEN IT OUTFOR ME?

17:31.759 --> 17:32.760
OUCH.

17:32.801 --> 17:35.095
ALL RIGHT.IS THAT OKAY?

17:35.137 --> 17:37.264
BEND IT BACK...

17:37.306 --> 17:39.016
IT'S GOOD.

17:39.057 --> 17:41.059
MIGHT BEA LITTLE BRUISED, 'KAY?

17:41.101 --> 17:42.519
MIGHT WANT TO PUT SOME ICEON IT WHEN YOU GET HOME.

17:42.561 --> 17:44.437
WILL DO.

17:44.438 --> 17:47.106
DR. GILSON... AS IN THE GILSON PEAR FARM?

17:47.107 --> 17:48.484
YEAH, THAT'S US.

17:48.525 --> 17:50.610
WOW, WE HAVEN'T SEENANY OF YOUR FAMILY HERE

17:50.611 --> 17:51.820
IN A LONG TIME.

17:51.862 --> 17:53.613
OH, YEAH, MOM AND DAD USEDTO COME UP ALL THE TIME

17:53.614 --> 17:54.740
FROM SEATTLE,

17:54.782 --> 17:55.991
BUT THEY ACTUALLY JOINEDAN ORGANIZATION

17:56.033 --> 17:57.618
THAT'S PROVIDING MEDICAL CAREOVERSEAS,

17:57.659 --> 17:58.869
SO THEY HAVEN'T BEEN BACK.

17:58.911 --> 18:00.537
ANDY AND IARE JUST HERE FOR A WEEK.

18:00.579 --> 18:01.789
OH, THAT'S A SHAME.

18:01.830 --> 18:03.623
YOU'LL MISSTHE HARVEST FESTIVAL.

18:03.624 --> 18:04.957
ANDY WOULD LOVE IT.

18:04.958 --> 18:07.169
PROBABLY.WE HAVE TO GET BACK, SO...

18:07.211 --> 18:08.294
[SIGHS]

18:08.295 --> 18:09.797
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

18:09.838 --> 18:10.714
SURE! I'M LUNA.

18:10.756 --> 18:12.633
NICOLE! PLEASURE.

18:12.674 --> 18:14.343
SAME.

18:14.384 --> 18:15.302
THEY LOOK HAPPY.

18:15.344 --> 18:16.386
YEAH.

18:16.428 --> 18:17.638
[ANDY]: SO THIS IS A PEAR.

18:17.679 --> 18:20.140
WE HAVE TONS OF THESEAT OUR FARM.

18:20.182 --> 18:21.183
AWESOME!

18:25.312 --> 18:30.025
♪ ♪

18:40.744 --> 18:42.412
[ROOSTER CROWING]

18:43.789 --> 18:45.541
[PHONE RINGS]

18:47.000 --> 18:48.334
HEY, MOM.

18:48.335 --> 18:51.755
[MOM]: HI, HONEY! I'M GLAD YOU'RE STILL UP.

18:51.797 --> 18:54.883
MOM, IT'S 10:00 A.M., NOT 10:00 P.M.

18:54.925 --> 18:58.345
OOPS, I'M NEVER GOING TO GETTHIS TIME DIFFERENCE RIGHT.

18:58.387 --> 18:59.721
SO HOW ARE YOU DOING?

18:59.763 --> 19:02.141
REALLY GOOD.I'M STILL IN MY PAJAMAS.

19:02.182 --> 19:03.642
I HAVEN'T BEEN ABLE TO DO THATIN YEARS.

19:03.684 --> 19:04.893
AW... AND HOW'S ANDY?

19:04.935 --> 19:07.187
ANDY'S GOOD,

19:07.229 --> 19:08.522
BUT I THINKHE'S A LITTLE DISAPPOINTED

19:08.564 --> 19:10.189
WE DIDN'T GO SOMEWHEREMORE EXCITING.

19:10.190 --> 19:11.942
HMM.

19:11.984 --> 19:14.193
WELL, JUST TELL HIM THE FARM'SNOT GOING TO BE THERE FOREVER,

19:14.194 --> 19:17.573
SO HE SHOULD APPRECIATE ITWHILE HE CAN.

19:17.614 --> 19:19.699
WHY WOULD I TELL HIM THAT?

19:19.700 --> 19:21.535
WELL, BECAUSE YOUR DAD AND IHAVE DECIDED

19:21.577 --> 19:23.035
TO PUT THE FARM UP FOR SALE.

19:23.036 --> 19:24.370
BUT WHY?

19:24.371 --> 19:26.707
WELL, NONE OF US ARE VERY INTERESTED IN IT,

19:26.748 --> 19:28.375
AND IT'S NOT MAKINGMUCH OF A PROFIT,

19:28.417 --> 19:30.169
SO IT DOESN'T SEEMTO MAKE MUCH SENSE

19:30.210 --> 19:31.587
TO HOLD ONTO IT ANYMORE.

19:31.628 --> 19:33.422
I SUPPOSE NOT.

19:36.258 --> 19:37.509
IT FEELS WEIRD TO THINK

19:37.551 --> 19:39.219
THAT THE FARM'S NOT GOINGTO BE IN THE FAMILY ANYMORE.

19:39.261 --> 19:41.722
I KNOW, BUT...

19:41.763 --> 19:43.974
MAYBE IT'S TIME WE ALL MADE A CHANGE.

19:54.276 --> 19:56.361
HI, THIS IS DR. GILSON.

19:56.403 --> 19:57.404
I UNDERSTAND

19:57.446 --> 19:58.905
THAT MR. MITCHELLIS BACK IN THE HOSPITAL.

19:58.906 --> 20:00.741
COULD YOU GIVE MEAN UPDATE ON HIS CONDITION?

20:00.782 --> 20:01.992
[LAUGHS]

20:02.034 --> 20:04.453
YES, I AM ON VACATION, BUT I JUST WANTED TO CHECK IN.

20:06.413 --> 20:07.747
WELL, PLEASE TELL DR. GORDON

20:07.748 --> 20:10.583
IF HE NEEDS TO CONSULT ME, HE CAN REACH ME ON MY CELL.

20:10.584 --> 20:13.085
NO, IT'S NO BOTHER AT ALL.

20:13.086 --> 20:14.713
OKAY, THANKS.

20:17.132 --> 20:18.675
HEY, I KNOWWE'RE ON VACATION,

20:18.717 --> 20:20.928
BUT I WANTEDTO CHECK IN ON A PATIENT.

20:20.969 --> 20:21.929
I'M SORRY.

20:21.970 --> 20:24.096
IT'S OKAY.

20:24.097 --> 20:26.683
IT'S NO DIFFERENTTHAN BEING AT HOME.

20:27.893 --> 20:29.101
YEAH, BUT EXCEPT AT HOME,

20:29.102 --> 20:31.355
WE'RE NOT SURROUNDEDBY ORCHARDS AND MOUNTAINS

20:31.396 --> 20:33.773
AND CLEAN AIR.

20:33.774 --> 20:35.317
YOU KNOW WHAT?

20:35.359 --> 20:36.610
IF YOU'RE DONEWITH YOUR BREAKFAST,

20:36.652 --> 20:37.861
THEN WHY DON'T YOU PUT AWAYYOUR COLORED PENCILS

20:37.903 --> 20:39.071
AND GRAB YOUR COAT,

20:39.112 --> 20:40.405
BECAUSE I WANT TO SHOW YOUSOMETHING SUPER COOL.

20:54.419 --> 20:56.088
WHOA...

20:59.925 --> 21:00.926
WOW!

21:02.177 --> 21:03.804
I FORGOT HOW BEAUTIFULTHIS PLACE IS.

21:03.845 --> 21:05.472
IT'S AWESOME, MOM.

21:05.514 --> 21:06.807
IT IS.

21:06.848 --> 21:09.976
"THE BEST PEAR GROUNDIS WHERE YOU CAN SEE PINE TREES

21:09.977 --> 21:11.436
WHEN YOU'RE STANDINGIN AN ORCHARD."

21:11.478 --> 21:13.021
HUH?

21:13.063 --> 21:15.023
I CAN'T BELIEVEI REMEMBERED THAT.

21:15.065 --> 21:18.277
MY GRANDPA GILSONUSED TO SAY IT ALL THE TIME.

21:19.361 --> 21:21.822
SO, ALL OF THESEARE PEAR TREES?

21:21.863 --> 21:24.991
YEP, AS FARAS THE EYE CAN SEE.

21:24.992 --> 21:26.743
YOU KNOW, WHEN I WAS YOUR AGE,

21:26.785 --> 21:28.537
I USED TO GO OUTINTO THE ORCHARD,

21:28.578 --> 21:29.829
AND I WOULD FIND A PEAR.

21:29.830 --> 21:31.039
I WOULD PICK IT,

21:31.081 --> 21:32.332
I WOULD TAKE A BITE,

21:32.374 --> 21:33.375
AND IT TASTEDJUST LIKE AUTUMN.

21:33.417 --> 21:36.295
AH, IT WAS HEAVENLY.

21:42.634 --> 21:44.094
LET'S TRY ONE.

21:46.847 --> 21:48.682
WHAT'S IT TASTE LIKE?

21:48.724 --> 21:50.434
NOT AUTUMN.

21:51.601 --> 21:53.520
THIS ONE'S NOT RIPE YET.COME ON, BUDDY.

22:04.614 --> 22:05.407
HEY.

22:05.449 --> 22:06.616
HI!

22:06.658 --> 22:08.035
SO, HOW DOES IT FEELTO BE BACK?

22:08.076 --> 22:10.703
IT FEELS GREAT.

22:10.704 --> 22:13.248
[ANDY]: UM, I'M KIND OF HUNGRY.

22:13.290 --> 22:15.375
CAN I GO INSIDEAND GET A SNACK?

22:15.417 --> 22:17.376
YEAH, THERE'S SOME GRANOLA BARSIN THE CUPBOARD.

22:17.377 --> 22:19.296
-THANKS.-MM-HMM.

22:19.337 --> 22:20.797
I HAVE A QUESTION FOR YOU.

22:20.839 --> 22:21.757
SHOOT.

22:21.798 --> 22:24.216
WHERE ARETHE RIPEST PEAR TREES?

22:24.217 --> 22:25.761
THOSE WOULD BE...

22:25.802 --> 22:26.762
OVER THERE,

22:26.803 --> 22:27.971
WHERE YOU THOUGHTI WAS STEALING THEM.

22:28.013 --> 22:29.389
YOU KNOW WHAT? YOU'LL SEE.

22:29.431 --> 22:31.433
ONE DAY, YOU'LL THINKTHAT'S A VERY FUNNY STORY.

22:31.475 --> 22:32.934
IT'S A FUNNY STORY NOW...

22:32.976 --> 22:33.894
LEAST THE WHOLE TOWN THOUGHT SO.

22:33.935 --> 22:34.895
WHAT?

22:34.896 --> 22:36.730
WELL, PINEVIEW'S A SMALL TOWN.

22:36.772 --> 22:38.065
WORD TRAVELS FAST.

22:38.106 --> 22:40.233
NOTED.

22:40.275 --> 22:41.359
[LAUGHS]

22:46.323 --> 22:47.407
[DOORBELL RINGS]

22:54.873 --> 22:56.166
-HI.-HI!

22:56.208 --> 22:57.583
[NICOLE]: I BROUGHT YOUA LASAGNE.

22:57.584 --> 22:59.336
I WANTED TO THANK YOUFOR YESTERDAY.

22:59.377 --> 23:00.629
OH, MY GOSH, THAT IS SO SWEET.

23:00.670 --> 23:02.254
PLEASE, COME IN.

23:02.255 --> 23:03.131
HI, BOBBY.

23:03.173 --> 23:04.299
HEY, ANDY.

23:04.341 --> 23:05.925
DO YOU PLAY SOCCER?

23:05.926 --> 23:06.927
YEAH.

23:06.968 --> 23:08.178
GREAT, BECAUSEI HAVE A BALL IN THE CAR.

23:08.220 --> 23:09.929
I WAS WONDERINGIF YOU WANTED TO KICK IT AROUND?

23:09.930 --> 23:11.014
SURE.

23:11.056 --> 23:12.099
COME ON, LET'S GO.

23:13.225 --> 23:14.935
BOBBY SEEMSNO WORSE FOR THE WEAR.

23:14.976 --> 23:17.436
LIKE IT NEVER EVEN HAPPENED.

23:17.437 --> 23:18.647
HOW ARE YOU TWOENJOYING THE FARM?

23:18.688 --> 23:19.981
I'M EASING INTO IT.

23:20.023 --> 23:23.443
IT'S NOT TOO QUIET OUT HEREFOR YOU, IS IT?

23:23.485 --> 23:24.778
QUIET IS EXACTLYWHAT WE NEED.

23:24.820 --> 23:26.113
I'VE BEEN SOBURNED OUT AT WORK,

23:26.154 --> 23:27.864
I'VE BARELY SPENTANY TIME WITH ANDY,

23:27.906 --> 23:30.449
SO IT'S BEEN THEPERFECT PLACE FOR US.

23:30.450 --> 23:31.785
MM.

23:34.704 --> 23:36.081
[HONKS HORN]

23:48.301 --> 23:50.636
SORRY IFI SCARED YOU ALL,

23:50.637 --> 23:52.472
BUT WE HAVE A BITOF AN EMERGENCY.

23:52.514 --> 23:54.099
I JUST GOT A CALLABOUT A TRACTOR ACCIDENT

23:54.141 --> 23:55.142
AT THE HENNESSY FARM,

23:55.183 --> 23:56.601
AND ONE OF THE FARMHANDSIS INJURED.

23:56.643 --> 23:58.477
THE AMBULANCE ISABOUT 30 MINUTES OUT,

23:58.478 --> 24:00.397
SO I WAS HOPINGTHAT DR. GILSON,

24:00.439 --> 24:01.565
YOU WOULD COME ONOUT THERE WITH ME

24:01.606 --> 24:02.648
AND SEE WHATYOU COULD DO.

24:02.649 --> 24:03.650
YEAH, OF COURSE.

24:03.692 --> 24:04.734
DON'T WORRY, I'LLSTAY WITH THE BOYS.

24:04.776 --> 24:05.735
THANKS.

24:05.777 --> 24:06.986
NEED MY HELP?

24:06.987 --> 24:08.405
YEAH, MIGHT NEEDAN EXTRA SET OF HANDS.

24:08.446 --> 24:09.322
ALL RIGHT, I'LL TAKE MY TRUCK.

24:09.323 --> 24:10.489
I'LL FOLLOW YOU OUT THERE.

24:10.490 --> 24:11.657
HANK, KEEP AN EYE ON THINGS'TIL I GET BACK.

24:11.658 --> 24:12.534
YEAH, OF COURSE.

24:12.576 --> 24:14.035
-YOU READY?-YEAH.

24:16.204 --> 24:18.665
YOUR MOM'S LIKEA SUPERHERO.

24:18.707 --> 24:20.167
YEAH...

24:20.208 --> 24:22.334
I GUESS SHE KIND OF IS.

24:22.335 --> 24:24.336
COME ON, BOYS, LET'S GO INSIDE.

24:24.337 --> 24:25.338
COME ON.

24:31.970 --> 24:33.096
UGH, GO ON, GIVE ME THE NEWS.

24:33.138 --> 24:34.139
HOW BAD IS IT?

24:35.849 --> 24:37.349
WELL, THE GOOD NEWS IS, YOU'RE GOING TO LIVE.

24:37.350 --> 24:40.103
THE BAD NEWS IS, I THINK IT'S A BROKEN TIBIA.

24:40.145 --> 24:41.354
I'M GOING TO NEEDTO STABILIZE YOUR LEG

24:41.396 --> 24:42.522
UNTIL THE AMBULANCE GETS HERE.

24:42.564 --> 24:44.524
DO WE HAVE ANYTHINGAROUND HERE WE CAN USE?

24:46.067 --> 24:47.402
SURE, IF THERE'SA COUPLE FENCE SLATS.

24:47.444 --> 24:48.403
WOULD THOSE WORK?

24:48.445 --> 24:49.529
YEAH, THAT SHOULD WORK.

24:53.658 --> 24:54.618
HERE.

24:54.659 --> 24:55.744
THANKS.

24:55.785 --> 24:56.745
OKAY.

24:56.786 --> 24:57.871
YOU'RE GOINGTO BE FINE.

24:57.913 --> 24:59.539
I'M GOING TO SPLINT YOUR LEGTO IMMOBILIZE IT.

24:59.581 --> 25:01.082
ONCE I DO THAT, WE'LL ELEVATE IT,

25:01.124 --> 25:02.875
AND YOUR PAIN SHOULD SUBSIDE.

25:02.876 --> 25:03.877
OKAY.

25:03.919 --> 25:05.377
EASY...

25:05.378 --> 25:06.421
[GRUNTS IN PAIN]

25:06.463 --> 25:08.340
GOOD JOB.HANG IN.

25:12.761 --> 25:14.554
[AMBULANCE ENGINE STARTS]

25:18.517 --> 25:20.101
HEY, SHERIFF, IT JUST DAWNED ON ME...

25:20.143 --> 25:22.062
HOW DID YOU KNOWI WAS A DOCTOR, HMM?

25:23.438 --> 25:24.397
DON'T LOOK AT ME.

25:24.398 --> 25:25.607
WELL, YOU KNOW,

25:25.649 --> 25:27.442
THERE'S NO SECRETSIN A SMALL TOWN.

25:27.484 --> 25:28.985
YEAH, SO I'VE BEEN TOLD.

25:29.027 --> 25:30.904
NICOLE'S MARRIEDTO MY COUSIN, TOM,

25:30.946 --> 25:34.449
AND I HEARD HOWYOU CHECKED OUT BOBBY'S KNEE.

25:34.491 --> 25:36.451
ANYHOW, I'M GOINGTO FOLLOW THE AMBULANCE.

25:36.493 --> 25:37.744
WILL, WOULD YOU MINDTAKING THE DOC HOME?

25:37.786 --> 25:38.912
YEAH, SURE.

25:38.954 --> 25:40.330
THANKS AGAIN, DR. GILSON.

25:40.372 --> 25:41.289
OF COURSE.

25:42.832 --> 25:44.917
HOW COME THIS TOWNDOESN'T HAVE A DOCTOR?

25:44.918 --> 25:46.253
I MEAN, IT'S NOT THAT SMALL.

25:46.294 --> 25:48.547
LAST ONE RETIRED.

25:48.588 --> 25:50.006
WE DO HAVETHREE VETERINARIANS, THOUGH.

25:50.048 --> 25:51.424
[LAUGHS]

25:55.095 --> 25:57.013
I'VE GOT TO SAY, DOC,

25:57.055 --> 25:58.932
YOUR MEDICAL SKILLSARE IMPRESSIVE...

25:58.974 --> 26:00.266
BETTER THANYOUR DRIVING SKILLS.

26:00.267 --> 26:01.433
OH, YEAH?

26:01.434 --> 26:03.144
AND TO THINKTHAT I HAVE BEEN DRIVING LONGER

26:03.186 --> 26:04.688
THAN I'VE BEENPRACTICING MEDICINE.

26:04.729 --> 26:06.106
I'M STILL THE ONEWHO GOT THE FLAT.

26:06.147 --> 26:07.274
WHICH WAS MY FAULT.

26:07.315 --> 26:09.192
YEAH, GUESS WE CAN AGREE ON THAT.

26:42.142 --> 26:43.184
HOW'D IT GO?

26:43.226 --> 26:45.186
HE HAS A BROKEN LEG,

26:45.228 --> 26:46.313
AND HE'S ON THE WAYTO THE HOSPITAL,

26:46.354 --> 26:47.480
SO HE SHOULD BE FINE.

26:47.522 --> 26:48.814
THANKS AGAIN SO MUCHFOR STAYING.

26:48.815 --> 26:49.816
OF COURSE.

26:49.858 --> 26:50.859
I THINKTHE BOYS HAD A GOOD TIME.

26:51.985 --> 26:53.987
BY THE WAY, I NOTICED A LEAKUNDER YOUR KITCHEN SINK.

26:54.029 --> 26:55.655
YOU DON'T WANTTO LET THAT GO TOO LONG.

26:55.697 --> 26:56.990
I WON'T. THANKSFOR LETTING ME KNOW.

