I THINKHE'S IN THE GREENHOUSE.

41:29.236 --> 41:30.738
THANKS.

41:45.002 --> 41:45.920
WILL?

41:45.961 --> 41:47.755
ARE YOU IN HERE?

42:06.607 --> 42:07.566
HEY, HANK.

42:07.608 --> 42:09.068
AH, HEY THERE, LUNA.

42:09.109 --> 42:11.320
CAN YOU POINT ME IN THEDIRECTION OF THE APPLE TREES?

42:11.362 --> 42:13.948
WE DON'T HAVE ANY APPLE TREES, JUST PEARS.

42:13.989 --> 42:15.449
YOU SURE?

42:15.491 --> 42:17.493
SURE AS I'M STANDING HERE.

42:17.534 --> 42:18.953
OH...

42:18.994 --> 42:21.079
THANKS.

42:21.080 --> 42:22.248
HAVE A GOOD WALK.

42:32.675 --> 42:34.009
I HEARD YOU WERELOOKING FOR ME.

42:34.051 --> 42:35.302
ACTUALLY, I WAS LOOKINGFOR AN APPLE

42:35.344 --> 42:37.179
LIKE THE ONE YOU GAVE ANDYYESTERDAY.

42:37.221 --> 42:38.597
HE SAID YOU GOT ITFROM ONE OF OUR TREES.

42:38.639 --> 42:40.431
WE DON'T HAVE APPLE TREES.

42:40.432 --> 42:41.432
BUT...

42:41.433 --> 42:43.101
SAW YOUIN TOWN EARLIER.

42:43.102 --> 42:44.269
OH, I DIDN'T THINK YOU DID.

42:44.270 --> 42:45.436
YOU SEEMED LIKE

42:45.437 --> 42:46.771
YOU WERE IN THE MIDDLEOF SOMETHING IMPORTANT.

42:46.772 --> 42:48.273
'CAUSE I WAS IN A SUIT?

42:48.274 --> 42:49.984
WELL, YOU DON'T DRESS LIKE THATEVERY DAY.

42:50.025 --> 42:51.068
WELL, IT WOULDN'T BE VERY PRACTICAL

42:51.110 --> 42:52.653
FOR AROUND THE FARM, NOW, WOULD IT?

42:52.695 --> 42:54.779
WELL, FARM BUSINESSDOESN'T ALWAYS HAPPEN ON A FARM,

42:54.780 --> 42:55.781
NOW, DOES IT?

42:56.865 --> 42:57.783
NO, IT DOESN'T,

42:57.825 --> 42:59.285
AND WHILE YOU'RE FISHING,

42:59.326 --> 43:00.452
WHY DON'T YOU CHECKOUT THE POND?

43:00.494 --> 43:02.454
[LAUGHS]

43:02.496 --> 43:03.455
I'LL SEE YOU, DOC.

43:03.497 --> 43:04.540
[STARTS ENGINE]

43:09.753 --> 43:10.754
[PHONE RINGS]

43:13.674 --> 43:14.966
HEY, MARCY, HOW ARE YOU?

43:14.967 --> 43:16.634
[MARCY]: YOU HAVEN'T CHECKED IN FOR A WHILE.

43:16.635 --> 43:17.970
I WAS BEGINNINGTO WONDER ABOUT YOU.

43:18.012 --> 43:19.888
OH, YEAH.I GUESS I FORGOT.

43:19.930 --> 43:21.140
THAT'S A FIRST.

43:21.181 --> 43:23.017
THEN THE TRIPMUST BE DOING YOU SOME GOOD.

43:23.058 --> 43:26.228
IT HAS... FOR BOTH OF US.

43:26.270 --> 43:28.355
I HAVEN'T SEEN ANDY THIS HAPPYIN YEARS.

43:29.732 --> 43:31.650
FORGOT HOW MUCHI LOVE IT HERE.

43:31.692 --> 43:33.902
SEE WHAT TAKING SOME TIME OFF CAN DO?

43:33.944 --> 43:35.571
BUT THE REASON I'M CALLING IS,

43:35.612 --> 43:37.031
YOU'LL BE BACK IN A FEW DAYS,

43:37.072 --> 43:40.701
SO SHOULD WE START SCHEDULINGSOME SURGERIES FOR NEXT WEEK?

43:40.743 --> 43:41.702
YEAH, OF COURSE...

43:45.289 --> 43:49.001
ON SECOND THOUGHT, DO YOU MIND IF I CALL YOU BACK?

43:49.043 --> 43:51.879
I KIND OF WANT TO HOLD OFFON MY SCHEDULE FOR A DAY OR TWO.

43:51.920 --> 43:52.963
OKAY.

43:53.005 --> 43:55.090
DON'T WAIT TOO LONG.

44:23.786 --> 44:24.787
[ATV ENGINE STARTS]

44:25.954 --> 44:27.206
MOM?

44:58.737 --> 44:59.822
YOU GOING SOMEWHERE?

44:59.863 --> 45:01.615
JUST OUT FOR A SPIN.

45:01.657 --> 45:02.699
YEAH, WELL,

45:02.741 --> 45:04.118
WE USUALLY TAKE THE ATV OUTFOR FARM WORK,

45:04.159 --> 45:05.119
NOT FOR JOY RIDES.

45:05.160 --> 45:06.328
WELL, I WAS CHECKING TO SEE

45:06.370 --> 45:07.913
IF THE PEARS ARE RIPE ENOUGHTO HARVEST.

45:07.955 --> 45:09.498
DO YOU EVEN KNOWWHAT YOU'RE LOOKING FOR?

45:09.540 --> 45:11.125
SORT OF.

45:11.166 --> 45:12.167
SORT OF.

45:12.209 --> 45:13.544
[PHONE TEXT CHIMES]

45:14.378 --> 45:15.421
HUH.

45:15.462 --> 45:17.089
SET UP FOR THE HARVESTFESTIVAL IS SHORTHANDED.

45:17.131 --> 45:18.257
COULD USE SOME VOLUNTEERS.

45:18.298 --> 45:19.925
OH, ANDY AND I CAN PITCH IN.

45:19.967 --> 45:20.926
ALL RIGHT, WELL, WE'LL TAKE MY TRUCK,

45:20.968 --> 45:22.261
NOT THE ATV.SCOOT OVER.

45:32.604 --> 45:33.564
[ENGINE STARTS]

45:56.712 --> 45:58.005
NOT VERY SUBTLE, ARE THEY?

46:01.049 --> 46:02.800
I THINK MOST OF THE SINGLEWOMEN IN PINEVIEW

46:02.801 --> 46:04.511
HAVE TRIED TO FLIRT WITH WILLAT ONE TIME OR ANOTHER.

46:04.553 --> 46:05.721
REALLY?

46:05.762 --> 46:07.806
YEAH, HE'S A GREAT CATCH.

46:07.848 --> 46:09.016
SWEETHEART!

46:09.057 --> 46:10.350
I JUST GOT A CALLCONFIRMING

46:10.392 --> 46:12.227
THAT FRANK HONEYWELL IS GOINGTO BE ONE OF THE JUDGES

46:12.269 --> 46:13.978
IN THE BEST PEAR COMPETITION!

46:13.979 --> 46:15.022
THAT'S QUITE A COUP FOR US.

46:15.063 --> 46:17.316
THAT'S WONDERFUL, HONEY!

46:17.357 --> 46:18.525
NOW WAIT, WHO IS HE AGAIN?

46:18.567 --> 46:19.568
[TOM]: HE'S ONE OFTHE BIGGEST FOOD DISTRIBUTORS

46:19.610 --> 46:20.611
IN THE STATE.

46:20.652 --> 46:22.653
WINNING OVERALL BEST PEARIS THE BRASS RING

46:22.654 --> 46:23.739
FOR ANY FARMER.

46:23.780 --> 46:25.199
A WIN LIKE THATCAN REALLY PUT YOU ON THE MAP.

46:25.240 --> 46:27.659
WELL, IT'S BEEN A WHILE, BUT IF I REMEMBER CORRECTLY,

46:27.701 --> 46:30.162
GILSON FARMS TOOK HOMETHAT PRIZE QUITE A FEW TIMES.

46:30.204 --> 46:31.830
NOT IN THE LAST SEVERAL YEARS.

46:31.872 --> 46:33.831
YEAH, WILLIAMSBURG FARMSHAS BEEN WINNING

46:33.832 --> 46:35.666
YEAR AFTER YEAR.

46:35.667 --> 46:37.336
OH, AND IREMEMBER THAT NAME.

46:37.377 --> 46:38.837
WHATEVER HAPPENEDTO THEIR SON, RONNY?

46:38.879 --> 46:41.006
HE WAS KIND OFA KNOW-IT-ALL?

46:41.048 --> 46:42.966
NO, NO, HE GOES BY RONALD NOW.

46:43.008 --> 46:45.219
YEAH, AND HE'S EVEN MOREOF A KNOW-IT-ALL.

46:45.260 --> 46:47.638
I GUESS SOME PEOPLENEVER CHANGE.

47:02.402 --> 47:03.403
I HEARD SOMEONE SAY

47:03.445 --> 47:04.780
THERE'S A HARVEST MOONSTARTING TONIGHT.

47:04.822 --> 47:06.364
YOU HEARD RIGHT.

47:06.365 --> 47:07.365
EVER SEEN ONE?

47:07.366 --> 47:09.034
UH, MAYBE WHEN I WAS YOUNGER,

47:09.076 --> 47:11.411
BUT I DON'T REMEMBER.

47:12.704 --> 47:13.789
LET'S SEE...

47:13.831 --> 47:16.750
THE HARVEST MOONHAPPENS ONCE A YEAR,

47:16.792 --> 47:19.419
AT THE BEGINNING OF AUTUMN,

47:19.461 --> 47:21.713
AND THE FULL MOON RISESAT SUNSET,

47:21.755 --> 47:23.215
SO IT'S BRIGHTERTHAN USUAL,

47:23.257 --> 47:24.967
WHICH MAKESFOR LONGER HARVEST DAYS.

47:25.968 --> 47:27.219
I AM IMPRESSED.

47:27.261 --> 47:29.555
MY GRANDPA TAUGHT ME THAT.

47:33.559 --> 47:36.270
WELL, IT LOOKS LIKEIT MIGHT BE A CLEAR NIGHT.

47:36.311 --> 47:38.730
I'LL BET WE'LL BE ABLETO GET A GOOD VIEW OF IT.

47:39.731 --> 47:40.941
WELL, IF YOU'RE NOT TOO TIRED LATER,

47:40.983 --> 47:42.609
I COULD SHOW YOUTHE BEST PLACE ON THE FARM

47:42.651 --> 47:43.652
TO SEE IT.

47:52.953 --> 47:54.538
WHY DON'T YOU LET ME HELP YOUWITH HIM?

47:58.876 --> 48:00.002
COME ON, BUDDY.

48:04.006 --> 48:05.465
COME ON, ANDY.

48:30.866 --> 48:32.367
GET HIMINTO BED ALL RIGHT?

48:32.409 --> 48:34.411
SURE DID.

48:35.746 --> 48:36.788
I REALLY WISH HECOULD HAVE SEEN IT

48:36.830 --> 48:39.041
BEFORE HE CONKED OUT.

48:41.793 --> 48:43.961
IT REALLY ISSOMETHING, ISN'T IT?

48:43.962 --> 48:46.632
YEP. YEAH.

48:46.673 --> 48:49.343
NOT GOING TO SEEANYTHING LIKE THAT IN SEATTLE.

48:49.384 --> 48:50.969
ALL THOSE CITY LIGHTS.

48:51.011 --> 48:53.513
AND TOO MUCH NOISE.

48:53.555 --> 48:56.975
I CAN ACTUALLY HEAR THECRICKETS CHIRPING HERE.

48:57.017 --> 48:58.809
[CHUCKLES]

48:58.810 --> 49:01.688
YOU HAVE BEEN IN THE CITYTOO LONG.

49:01.730 --> 49:02.689
THOSE ARE FROGS.

49:02.731 --> 49:04.399
WHAT? NO!

49:04.441 --> 49:06.360
YES, THOSE ARE FROGS.

49:06.401 --> 49:07.527
ARE YOU SURE?

49:07.569 --> 49:08.820
PRETTY SURE.

49:08.862 --> 49:10.364
OKAY, WELL,

49:10.405 --> 49:12.157
WHATEVER THAT NOISE IS,

49:12.199 --> 49:15.826
IT'S... IT'S VERY RELAXING.

49:15.827 --> 49:18.163
THAT'S SOMETHINGI DON'T THINK YOU DO MUCH OF.

49:20.207 --> 49:22.167
YEAH, WELL, WHEN YOU HAVEA EIGHT-YEAR-OLD KID,

49:22.209 --> 49:23.335
AND YOU'RE ANON-CALL SURGEON,

49:23.377 --> 49:24.336
YOU DON'T REALLYHAVE TIME

49:24.337 --> 49:26.004
TO STOP ANDSMELL THE ROSES...

49:27.965 --> 49:31.342
OR THE APPLES, IT SEEMS.

49:31.343 --> 49:33.844
COME ON, WHAT'S YOURSECRET, WILL NASH?

49:33.845 --> 49:36.056
I DON'T HAVE A SECRET.

49:36.098 --> 49:38.266
I JUST DON'T REVEAL MUCH.

49:38.308 --> 49:40.894
YEAH, WELL, THAT MIGHT BEA GOOD IDEA FOR BUSINESS,

49:40.936 --> 49:42.688
BUT DOESN'T THATGET IN THE WAY

49:42.729 --> 49:44.356
OF HAVING A RELATIONSHIP?

49:44.398 --> 49:46.233
WHO SAYS I WANT ONE?

49:46.274 --> 49:48.944
I WASN'T... IMPLYING THAT.

49:48.985 --> 49:50.612
I JUST... I MEANT...

49:50.654 --> 49:53.198
I MEANT THAT MOSTPEOPLE DO THAT

49:53.240 --> 49:55.366
AT SOME POINTOR ANOTHER, SO...

49:55.367 --> 49:58.704
WELL, MAYBEAT SOME POINT, I WILL.

50:02.416 --> 50:04.751
YEAH, BUTI DON'T GET IT.

50:04.793 --> 50:06.294
I MEAN, YOU'REA GOOD CATCH, WILL.

50:06.336 --> 50:08.213
NICOLE'S WORDS, NOT MINE...

50:08.255 --> 50:09.380
BUT IT ISMY UNDERSTANDING

50:09.381 --> 50:12.384
THAT YOU'RE VERY POPULARWITH THE LOCAL LADIES.

50:12.426 --> 50:13.802
[LAUGHS]

50:14.970 --> 50:16.887
LET'S JUST SAYTHAT A RELATIONSHIP

50:16.888 --> 50:19.057
DOESN'T EXACTLY FITINTO MY PLAN RIGHT NOW.

50:19.099 --> 50:21.685
WHICH YOU'RE NOTGOING TO TELL ME.

50:21.727 --> 50:23.729
YOU ARE PERSISTENT, AREN'T YOU?

50:27.441 --> 50:30.610
OWNING MY OWN FARM, OKAY? THAT'S MY PLAN.

50:30.652 --> 50:32.571
THAT'S A NICE PLAN!

50:35.115 --> 50:35.949
I DON'T REALLYUNDERSTAND

50:35.991 --> 50:36.867
HOW HAVINGA RELATIONSHIP

50:36.908 --> 50:39.744
GETS IN THE WAYOF THAT, THOUGH.

50:39.745 --> 50:41.830
SOMETIMES, THEY DO.

50:47.711 --> 50:51.214
WHEN I WAS IN MEDICAL SCHOOL, I HAD A PLAN, TOO.

50:52.591 --> 50:56.260
NO DISTRACTIONSUNTIL I FINISHED MY RESIDENCY...

50:56.261 --> 50:57.763
AND THEN I MET PHILLIP,

50:57.804 --> 50:59.890
AND MY PLAN SORT OF FLEWOUT THE WINDOW.

51:02.100 --> 51:04.019
GLAD IT WORKED OUTFOR YOU, DOC.

51:06.813 --> 51:09.983
WHEN I MET SOMEBODY, THREW MY PLANS OUT THE WINDOW...

51:10.025 --> 51:11.359
IT DIDN'T EXACTLY WORK OUTFOR ME.

51:11.401 --> 51:13.987
I WAS BLINDSIDED.

51:14.029 --> 51:16.031
YEAH, THINGS DON'T ALWAYS GOAS YOU PLANNED.

51:23.413 --> 51:24.372
MUST HAVE BEEN HARD.

51:26.917 --> 51:28.210
IT WAS.

51:31.379 --> 51:33.423
IT STILL IS, SOMETIMES...

51:36.802 --> 51:38.261
BUT I HAVE ANDY...

51:39.679 --> 51:42.057
ALTHOUGH I'VE SHORTCHANGED HIMA LOT LATELY.

51:44.059 --> 51:45.018
HOW DO YOU MEAN?

51:46.770 --> 51:49.313
I THREW MYSELF INTO WORK,

51:49.314 --> 51:52.901
AND I WASN'T REALLY AROUNDFOR ANDY ENOUGH.

51:55.278 --> 51:57.489
THE WHOLE POINT OF THIS TRIPWAS TO RECONNECT WITH HIM,

51:57.531 --> 52:00.951
WHICH I THINKI'VE MANAGED TO DO.

52:03.787 --> 52:04.746
WHAT HAPPENSWHEN YOU GO BACK

52:04.788 --> 52:06.081
IN A COUPLE DAYS?

52:09.709 --> 52:11.753
TO BE HONEST, I DON'T KNOW.

52:42.075 --> 52:43.785
UP KIND OF EARLY, AREN'T YOU?

52:45.287 --> 52:47.247
COULDN'T SLEEP.

52:47.289 --> 52:49.039
THE MOON GIVE YOUA LOT TO THINK ABOUT?

52:49.040 --> 52:50.750
IT DID.

52:54.254 --> 52:55.380
[PHONE RINGS]

52:59.092 --> 53:00.635
DO YOU NEED TO GET THAT?

53:00.677 --> 53:01.719
[TURNS IT OFF]

53:01.720 --> 53:03.638
YEAH...

53:03.680 --> 53:06.391
BUT I'M NOT READY TO.

53:08.894 --> 53:09.895
ENJOY YOUR WALK, LUNA.

53:23.950 --> 53:25.202
[WILL]: DON'T FORGET TO DOTHE LIFT AND TWIST.

53:25.243 --> 53:27.244
OKAY, WILL,

53:27.245 --> 53:29.998
YOU REALLY HAVE TO STOPSNEAKING UP BEHIND PEOPLE.

53:30.040 --> 53:31.166
MAYBE IF CERTAIN PEOPLESTOPPED SHOWING UP

53:31.208 --> 53:32.249
WHERE THEY'RE NOTSUPPOSED TO...

53:32.250 --> 53:34.084
AND WHY AM I NOT SUPPOSEDTO BE HERE?

53:34.085 --> 53:36.504
JUST THAT THESE TREES ARE STILLIN THE DEVELOPMENTAL PHASE.

53:36.546 --> 53:37.714
YEAH, WELL, IF IT'S THE SAME FRUIT

53:37.756 --> 53:39.089
THAT YOU GAVE ANDYTHE OTHER DAY,

53:39.090 --> 53:40.592
I WOULD SAYIT'S FAR MORE THAN DEVELOPED.

53:40.634 --> 53:42.552
IT'S AMAZING.

53:43.845 --> 53:46.431
SO, WHAT IS ALL THIS?

53:46.473 --> 53:47.766
WELL, FIRST OF ALL,

53:47.807 --> 53:51.019
THEY'RE NOT APPLES, THEY'RE PEARS.

53:51.061 --> 53:52.436
I CROSSBREDA RARE VARIETY OF RED SECKEL

53:52.437 --> 53:53.604
WITH AN ASIAN SEURI,

53:53.605 --> 53:55.690
SO THEY HAVE THE LOOKAND COLORING OF AN APPLE,

53:55.732 --> 53:57.275
BUT THE SEURI FLAVORHAS HINTS OF APRICOT.

53:57.317 --> 53:59.610
SO THAT'S WHY IT WAS SO SWEET.

53:59.611 --> 54:01.863
MM-HMM, THEY ALSO HAVEA LONGER STORAGE LIFE

54:01.905 --> 54:04.115
AND LESS SUSCEPTIBILITYTO BRUISING.

54:04.157 --> 54:05.783
THAT'S BRILLIANT.

54:05.784 --> 54:08.161
SO DOES THIS FRUITHAVE A NAME YET?

54:08.203 --> 54:09.453
NOT YET.

54:09.454 --> 54:11.622
THE SCIENTIFIC NAMEIS PYRUS PHOENICEUS.

54:11.623 --> 54:12.999
I PATENTED IT.

54:13.041 --> 54:13.959
I'M BEINGA LITTLE CAUTIOUS

54:14.000 --> 54:15.043
ABOUT WHATMY NEXT STEP IS.

54:15.085 --> 54:18.046
SO THAT EXPLAINS THE SECRECY.

54:18.088 --> 54:19.296
I MET WITH SOMEPOTENTIAL INVESTORS,

54:19.297 --> 54:20.465
BUT THEY'RE NOT SOLD YET,

54:20.507 --> 54:22.634
SO I ENTERED ITIN THE HARVEST FESTIVAL,

54:22.676 --> 54:24.969
AND IF IT WINS BEST OVERALL, THAT COULD SEAL THE DEAL.

54:24.970 --> 54:27.305
HMM.

54:27.347 --> 54:30.642
SO WHY DON'T YOU JUST CONTINUETO GROW THEM HERE?

54:30.684 --> 54:31.559
I COULD NEVER AFFORDTO DO THAT

54:31.601 --> 54:33.561
ON A FARM THIS LARGE.

54:33.603 --> 54:35.689
BESIDES, IF YOUR PARENTSACTUALLY FIND A BUYER,

54:35.730 --> 54:38.024
THIS FARM MAY NOTEVEN BE HERE ANYMORE.

54:38.066 --> 54:39.651
THAT'S WHAT HAPPENEDWITH MY FOLKS.

54:39.693 --> 54:40.944
YEAH, FARLEY TOLD ME

54:40.986 --> 54:43.113
THAT A CORPORATIONTOOK IT OVER.

54:43.154 --> 54:44.114
YEAH.

54:44.155 --> 54:45.740
LEVELED IT.

54:45.782 --> 54:47.909
TURNED IT INTOA SHOPPING MALL.

54:47.951 --> 54:49.536
THAT'S AWFUL.

54:49.577 --> 54:51.371
IT WAS,

54:51.413 --> 54:54.708
BUT TAUGHT ME THATWHEN LIFE KNOCKS YOU DOWN,

54:54.749 --> 54:56.167
YOU GET BACK UP,

54:56.209 --> 54:58.211
SO THAT'S WHAT I DID,

54:58.253 --> 55:00.797
AND THAT'SWHAT I'M DOING.

55:08.555 --> 55:10.140
ANDY, HONEY, THERE'S SOMETHINGI WANT TO DISCUSS WITH YOU.

55:11.349 --> 55:13.518
FIRST OF ALL, I WANT YOU TO KNOW

55:13.560 --> 55:16.354
THAT I AM SO SORRYFOR ALL THE PLAYS,

55:16.396 --> 55:17.521
AND THE SPELLING BEES,

55:17.522 --> 55:20.358
AND THE SOCCER GAMESTHAT I MISSED.

55:20.400 --> 55:21.443
YOU DESERVE A MOM

55:21.484 --> 55:23.945
THAT'S GOING TO BE THEREFOR YOU, 'KAY?

55:23.987 --> 55:27.115
AND I'M HOPING THAT THISMAKES UP FOR THAT A LITTLE.

55:27.157 --> 55:28.700
I KNOW IT'S NOT A THEME PARK,

55:28.742 --> 55:32.245
OR WHAT YOU REALLY WANTEDTO DO, BUT...

55:32.287 --> 55:34.372
THIS HASN'T BEEN SO BAD,

55:34.414 --> 55:36.541
AND IT'S BEEN KIND OF FUNWATCHING YOU TRY TO BAKE.

55:36.583 --> 55:37.751
[LAUGHS]

55:37.792 --> 55:40.044
YEAH, WELL, I... YOU KNOW WHAT?

55:40.045 --> 55:41.004
YOU'RE GOING TO SEE.

55:41.046 --> 55:42.088
I AM GOINGTO MASTER THAT COBBLER...

55:42.130 --> 55:43.089
MM-HMM.

55:43.131 --> 55:44.299
AND YOU ARE GOING TO LOVE IT.

55:44.340 --> 55:45.883
HONEY, IF YOU HAD A CHOICE,

55:45.884 --> 55:48.428
WOULD YOU WANT TO GO BACKTO SEATTLE AS PLANNED,

55:48.470 --> 55:50.220
OR WOULD YOU MAYBE WANTTO STICK AROUND HERE

55:50.221 --> 55:51.222
A LITTLE LONGER?

55:51.264 --> 55:54.059
COULD WE STAYFOR THE HARVEST FESTIVAL?

55:54.100 --> 55:57.145
THAT IS EXACTLYWHAT I WAS THINKING.

55:57.187 --> 55:58.730
OF COURSE, YOU'D HAVETO DO SOME SCHOOL WORK.

55:58.772 --> 56:02.067
I THINK I COULD CALL SCHOOLAND GET YOUR ASSIGNMENTS, BUT...

56:02.108 --> 56:03.360
I WANT TO STAY.

56:03.401 --> 56:05.445
YOU DIDN'T EVEN HEAR THE PARTABOUT SCHOOL, DID YOU?

56:05.487 --> 56:06.571
I GET IT.

56:06.613 --> 56:09.365
IF WE STAY, I STILL HAVE TO STUDY.

56:09.407 --> 56:10.575
YES.

56:10.617 --> 56:12.827
ALL RIGHT, I GUESS WE'RE GOINGTO STAY A LITTLE LONGER.

56:12.869 --> 56:14.913
AHEM.

56:14.954 --> 56:15.914
HELLO THERE, LUNA.

56:15.955 --> 56:17.165
WELL, HELLO, RONNY.

56:17.207 --> 56:18.166
YOU REMEMBER ME.

56:18.208 --> 56:20.084
YOU'RE NOT EASY TO FORGET.

56:20.085 --> 56:22.462
ANDY, THIS ISRONNY WILLIAMSBURG.

56:22.504 --> 56:24.089
OH, IT'S RONALD NOW.

56:24.130 --> 56:26.841
I HEAR YOUR FARMIS UP FOR SALE.

56:26.883 --> 56:28.426
MUST BE WHAT BROUGHT YOUBACK TO TOWN.

56:28.468 --> 56:30.804
NO, IT'S NOT.WE'RE ON VACATION.

56:30.845 --> 56:32.013
OH, THEN PERHAPSI'LL SEE YOU

56:32.055 --> 56:33.765
AT THE HARVEST FESTIVAL.

56:33.807 --> 56:35.100
YOU'LL SEE ME THERE,

56:35.141 --> 56:36.684
UP ON STAGE.

56:36.726 --> 56:40.355
MY FARM HAS WON THE TOP PRIZESEVEN CONSECUTIVE YEARS.

56:40.396 --> 56:42.649
YOU MEANYOUR FAMILY'S FARM, RIGHT?

56:44.400 --> 56:46.110
SO NICE TO SEE YOU AGAIN, LUNA.

56:46.111 --> 56:47.862
YOU TOO, RONNY.

